4: It's okay, you know it's coming.
19:
Marina... How many times have I told
you to knock? You never hesitate to—
23:
What's the matter—cat got your
tongue? Isn't Czarina's new outfit
just—
27:
The COOLEST! What is that?! You
look like the pilot of a giant robot!
36:
Where'd you get something so cool?
I want one...
41: Well, this wasn't what I expected.
46:
Oh come on, who wouldn't think this
is amazing?! It looks like you could
even fly—
64:
Who knew Al was such a nerd for
mech stuff? What a letdown...
72:
Come on, Al, take a closer look. Look
at how FORM-FITTING it is.
75:
I mean, it really leaves nothing to
the imagination.
88:
Aha! You can't look her in the eye
now, can you? 'Bout time you figured
it out!
102:
What is WITH everyone?! Do you all
get some sick pleasure out of
teasing me?!
105:
It's not just you two either!
Inaho—heck, even LILITH is doing it
now! Is this some new trend?! How
would YOU like it if I did the same
thing to you?! Huh? HUH?!
125:
It's fine. Besides. It's just clothes.
Nothing to get upset about, right?
Yes. That's right.
130:
Aw, come on, I know we got carried
away, but we said we're sorry, didn't
we?
138:
Well, most people toy with ME by
saying I don't have an ounce of sex
appeal, so I guess this means we're
even.
142:
What are you talking about? Your
crew must be messing with you.
149:
Huh? Awww, where'd that come
from?
155: Al! Al! What did you just DO?!
160:
N-nothing! I just gave her a little
complime—
166:
Well, DO IT AGAIN! Look at how
adorable my Czarina is when she's
blushing!
171:
Hehehe. Yeah, let's hear more of
those compliments. I can take it.
180:
Anyway, enough fooling around. I
need your help with something, Alk.
182:
I want to ask you, not as a Crimson
Blade, but as a citizen of Starview
Village, to help me...
188:
Raid Qualia City? Now that sounds
like fun!
198:
U-um... Why are you inviting me
along?
203:
Why wouldn't I? You're my precious
friend, aren't you? And you've got
experience to boot.
208:
Uh... How exactly are you choosing
people here?
219:
Hehehe... With this crew, we're bound
to win no matter what comes our
way!
222: You, uh... planning to start a war?
226:
Speaking of hot-blooded, there's
one more crewmate I need. Where's
Nimbus?
230:
Ah... You better see for yourself. He's
in a... shocking predicament.
241:
It's like a switch flipped inside him
while he was training with Taiga...
But now he can't turn that switch
OFF.
246:
Gotcha... Looks like you're sitting this
one out, buddy.
253:
The hell I am! I'm going, even if I
have to crawl there! Worst case
scenario, you can use me as a
bomb or—
257:
Yeah, and make Couette cry? I don't
think so.
260:
Well, I'm sure we'll figure something
out. Besides, I know a certain sparky
someone who might be able to help
you out.
264:
Now that THAT'S settled, let's grab
Couette and head out!
277:
Uhhh... Couldn't you come up with
something better to say?
